Class JFieldReference

java.lang.Object
org.jtool.cfg.JReference
org.jtool.cfg.JFieldReference
public class JFieldReference

    • JFieldReference

      public JFieldReference​(org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.ASTNode node, java.lang.String className, java.lang.String name, java.lang.String referenceForm, java.lang.String type, boolean primitive, int modifiers, boolean inProject, boolean visible)
      Creates a new object that represents a reference to a field.
      Parameters:
      node - the AST node corresponding to this reference
      className - the name of a class declaring the referenced field
      name - the name of the referenced field
      referenceForm - the form of this reference
      type - the type of the referenced field
      primitive - true if the type of the referenced field is primitive, otherwise false
      modifiers - the modifier information on the referenced field
      inProject - true if the referenced field exists in the target project, otherwise false
      visible - true if this is a reference to a visible field, otherwise false
